                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.00 Economic Non-Aggression/8: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-16T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 16, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>138. Your despatch No. 2260, September 30, 1931. You are directed to acknowledge
                    receipt in the usual informal manner of the Secretary-General’s communication to
                    me of September 29th, and to embody in your acknowledgment the following “In
                    reply, the United States Government, while thanking the Council of the League of
                    Nations for its courtesy in extending this invitation, does not expect to
                    participate in the work of this committee.”<note n="38" xml:id="d462fn38">A
                        memorandum of October 13, 1931, prepared in the Division of Western European
                        Affairs states: “… The pact itself is in very general terms; and appears to
                        offer nothing sufficiently practical to justify our acceptance of the
                        invitation. Nobody in Geneva seems to have taken it very seriously…”</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
